    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so if the main problem is just \"enforcement,\" does that mean the institutional structure itself is actually solid? or are some historians arguing that the system is fundamentally broken because it relies on the very powers that cause the problems in the first place? like, is the \"safety net\" argument just an excuse to keep a system that doesn't actually work for most people?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
